{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry represents blue-light-absorbing [[cite:PUB00042683]] and green-light absorbing [[cite:PUB00042684]] proteorhodopsins, as well as predicted bacterial type rhodopsins. Proteorhodopsins (PRs), the recently discovered light-driven proton pumps, play a major role in supplying energy for microbial organisms of oceans and belong to the archaeal/bacterial/fungal opsin family [[cite:PUB00042685]]. Blue-light absorbing proteorhodopsin may have a regulatory rather than energy harvesting function, based on light-induced opening of proton channels, to modulate cell physiology depending on light intensity variations, and could be a sensory rhodopsin, potentially associated with a transducer component. Blue-light absorbing proteorhodopsin presents a much slower photocycle than that of the green-absorbing proteorhodopsin. Green-light absorbing proteorhodopsin generates photothrophic energy, with a fast proton release and an alkaliphilic photocycle.</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "3ddl", "name" "Crystallographic Structure of Xanthorhodopsin, a Light-Driven Ion Pump with Dual Chromophore"}, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"pirsf" {"PIRSF038142" "Predicted rhodopsin, bacterial type"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Proteorhodopsin", "short" "Proteorhodopsin"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 10, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 119, "taxa" 1019, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 1255, "sets" 0, "proteins" 1255, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 1006}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR017402", :literature {"PUB00042683" {"URL" nil, "issue" "6", "authors" ["Imasheva ES" "Balashov SP" "Wang JM" "Dioumaev AK" "Lanyi JK."], "ISO_journal" "Biochemistry", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1021/bi0355894", "medline_journal" "Bioc